<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">A similar protest was held outside the Chinese consulate in Chiang Mai on July 6, where demonstrators from the People&#8217;s Network to Protect the Kok, Sai, Ruak, and Mekong Rivers said they were confronted by police while attempting to submit a petition.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Two protesters were reportedly injured, including one who underwent surgery for a broken arm, though Chiang Mai police maintained that officers &#8220;followed standard procedure&#8221; and denied any intention to use force against demonstrators.</p>
<p>This prompted a Bangkok protester to hold up a sign which said: &#8220;This is Thailand, not <a href="https://thethaiger.com/guides/thirty-seven-years-tiananmen-square" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tiananmen</a>.&#8221;</p>
